<P>But for the amb<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">&s;&s;<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">dors, per&s;ec<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">tion had never born known in the world, &s;ir. The laity have &s;o little zeal for God, that they would, if not in&s;tigated by the clergy, &s;uffer
<PB N="213" REF="027249_0211_0FD3ED50D9D90CD8">men to wor&s;hip him according to the be&s;t under&s;tanding they have of his mind revealed in the bible. But the amba&s;&s;a|dors are quite of another opinion; for by them it is deter|mined, that God &s;hall be wor&s;hipped in the very mode by them directed, or he &s;hall not be wor&s;hipped at all, if they can help it. The honour of per&s;ecution, alias, puni&s;hing of he|reties, mu&s;t all be a&s;cribed to the reverend amba&s;&s;adors.</P>
